@node play "How to play"

                                How to play?

  To play, each player click on a tile where he (or she) wants to move his (her)
Knight. That move must follow the Knights move on a Chess board, that is, an "L"
move (2 spaces horizontally (or vertically) and 1 space vertically (or
horizontally)). If the move is possible, the Knight will go there. When a Knight
leaves a position, its last position is marked by the player's colour, that tile
cannot be used again by either players.

  The number of tiles each player has is indicated under the players icon
(displayed on each side of the game board). When its a players turn to play, his
(her) icon is surronded by a box with the players colour.

  The game continues as long as there are spaces where a player can move to. If
a player cannot move, the other player will continue until he (or she) cannot
move. If both players are tied, (I.E.: with the same number of tiles), the game
goes in overtime and displays a new clean board and the game continues. Each
player starts at the position he (she) was on the last board.

  When run, Game_of_Knights displays its main menu where you can choose the
options you (and your opponent) prefer to use during a game. these options
are:

 -@{b}Knight Colours@{ub}:         Click on a Knight icon to change its colour.

 -@{b}Take opponent's Knight@{ub}: If this option is set to 'Yes', it allows to
                          'take' the opponent's Knight. When the opponent is
                          'taken', his (her) Knight is removed from the board
                          and he (she) cannot continue to play... just like
                          the Chess game!

  Click on the 'Play!' button to play a game.

  Note that you can abort a game at any time by clicking on the windows
closebutton, which will bring back the main menu.

@endnode

